# Agent skills

@summary
Author agent skills in Lessmark and emit native SKILL.md bundles for
the tools that load them.

Codex, Claude, and the open Agent Skills format use a folder with a
{{code:SKILL.md}} file at runtime. Lessmark does not replace that
runtime contract. It gives the author a typed source file, validation,
canonical formatting, and deterministic build output.

## Source shape

@code lang="lessmark"
@skill name="code-review" description="Review code for bugs, regressions, security issues, and missing tests."

When reviewing code, lead with findings.

@constraint
Do not rewrite unrelated files.

@task status="todo"
Inspect the diff before suggesting changes.

@file path="references/checklist.lmk"
Use this reference for deeper reviews.

The skill source is the file people and agents edit. Generated
{{code:SKILL.md}} files are build output.

## Bundle shape

@code lang="text"
code-review/
  skill.lmk
  references/
  scripts/
  build/
    codex/
      SKILL.md
      references/
      scripts/
    claude/
      SKILL.md
      references/
      scripts/

## Commands

@code lang="sh"
lessmark skill init code-review
lessmark skill check code-review
lessmark skill build code-review --target both
lessmark skill import code-review/SKILL.md --out code-review/skill.lmk
lessmark skill install code-review --target codex
lessmark skill install code-review --target claude
lessmark skill dev code-review

@table columns="Command|What it does"
init|Creates skill.lmk, references/, and scripts/.
check|Validates the Lessmark source and referenced resource paths.
build|Writes native SKILL.md bundles under build/codex and build/claude.
import|Converts an existing SKILL.md into a Lessmark skill source.
install|Writes a repo-scoped native skill for Codex or Claude.
dev|Watches the Lessmark source and rebuilds the bundle.

## Generated SKILL.md

@code lang="md"
---
name: "code-review"
description: "Review code for bugs, regressions, security issues, and missing tests."
---

When reviewing code, lead with findings.

> Constraint: Do not rewrite unrelated files.

- [ ] Inspect the diff before suggesting changes.

**File:** `references/checklist.lmk`

Use this reference for deeper reviews.

## Targets

@table columns="Target|Install path"
codex|.agents/skills/name/SKILL.md
claude|.claude/skills/name/SKILL.md
both|Build or install both native bundles.

## Why this is not two-source editing

@list kind="unordered"
- Edit {{code:skill.lmk}}.
- Run {{code:lessmark skill build}} or {{code:lessmark skill dev}}.
- Commit generated bundles only when the target tool needs them in the repo.
- Do not hand-edit generated {{code:SKILL.md}} files.

## Portable core

The portable Lessmark skill block supports {{code:name}},
{{code:description}}, {{code:license}}, {{code:compatibility}}, and
{{code:allowed-tools}}. Keep vendor-specific behavior out of the source
unless a target adapter needs it.
